 from tbigham shearson com tim bigham subject re advice on bmws and winter driving reply to tbigham shearson com organization lehman brothers inc lines two six this past winter i drove from nyc to killington vt six or seven times in my one nine nine zero three two five i convertible talk about poor reputation in the snow with an excellent set of snow tires i put four noika nr one zero s on in dec and have been sure footed in some pretty severe weather conditions ever since i ve plowed through four five inch snow covered roads effortlessly while other cars have been paralyzed front wheel drive included concentrate more on where the rubber meets the road rather than driveability of cars in snowy conditions drive carefully buy good snow tires and most cars will perform adequately in less than ideal conditions an aside i can t praise noika nr one zero snows enough absolutely the best snow tires i have ever driven on if you live in the snow belt do yourself a favor and get a set of these next winter tim timothy j bigham all opinions expressed above are my own lehman brothers inc and should not be construed as those of amex tower world financial center my employer new york n y